verbs.description: intertwine (third-person singular simple present intertwines, present participle intertwining, simple past and past participle intertwined)

examples: You see, no doubt, that yet again, thanks to this intertwining, our many-headed sophist has forced us against our will to admit that what is not is in a way.

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To become twined together; to become mutually involved.
